'''Plus Tate''' is a network of [[visual arts]] organisations in the [[United Kingdom]], led by the [[Tate]] gallery in [[London]].
Plus Tate was launched by [[Jeremy Hunt]] MP in 2012,<ref name="gov.uk">{{cite web| url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/jeremy-hunt-launches-plus-tate | title=Jeremy Hunt launches Plus Tate | website=[[GOV.UK]] | publisher=[[Government of the United Kingdom]] | location=UK | date=20 May 2012 | accessdate=18 October 2017 }}</ref> initially with 18 partners.<ref name="ft" /> 16 new institutions were added to the network in 2015,<ref name="a-n">{{cite web| url=https://www.a-n.co.uk/news/plus-tate-adds-16-new-institutions-to-uk-wide-network | title=Plus Tate adds 16 new institutions to UK-wide network | website=www.a-n.co.uk | publisher=a.n | location=UK | first=Chris | last=Sharratt | date=26 March 2015 | accessdate=18 October 2017 }}</ref> increasing the size of the network to 35 members, as announced by [[Nicholas Serota]].<ref name="ft">{{cite web| url=https://www.ft.com/content/23b81fb6-cf07-11e4-893d-00144feab7de?mhq5j=e7 | title=How Tate is strengthening the state of the arts | newspaper=[[Financial Times]] | first=Nicholas | last=Serota | authorlink=Nicholas Serota | date=25 March 2015 | accessdate=18 October 2017 }}</ref> {{Asof|2015}}, Plus Tate member institutions were visited by more than 3.5m people annually, employing around 500 staff, with an annual turnover of around £33 million.<ref name="cvan">{{cite web| url=http://www.cvan.org.uk/news/2015/1/14/plus-tate-research-shows-role-of-visuals-arts-in-regeneration | title=Plus Tate research shows role of visuals [sic] arts in regeneration | website=www.cvan.org.uk | publisher=Contemporary Visual Arts Network | location=UK | date=14 January 2015 | accessdate=18 October 2017 }}</ref>
