{{Infobox book | name = The Brutal Telling | image = The Brutal Telling.jpg | author = [[Louise Penny]] | genre = [[Mystery fiction]] | published = 2009 | publisher = [[Minotaur Books]] | isbn = 978-0-312-37703-8 | alt = The Brutal Telling | pages = 372 | website = {{URL|http://www.louisepenny.com/books.htm#ex_tbt|The Brutal Telling}} | awards = [[Anthony Award|Anthony Award for Best Novel]] (2010) }} '''The Brutal Telling''' is a novel written by [[Louise Penny]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=uIgPiYgzrhAC&source=gbs_navlinks_s|title=The Brutal Telling|last=Penny|first=Louise|date=2011-04-07|publisher=Little, Brown Book Group|isbn=9780748129621|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.louisepenny.com/books.htm#ex_tbt|title=Louise Penny Author - Official site|website=www.louisepenny.com|access-date=2017-03-26}}</ref>, part of the [[Chief Inspector Armand Gamache]] series. It was published by [[Minotaur Books]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-312-37703-8|title=Fiction Book Review: The Brutal Telling by Louise Penny|work=PublishersWeekly.com|access-date=2017-03-26|language=en}}</ref>, an imprint of [[St. Martin's Press]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/brutal-telling-louise-penny/1100162370|title=The Brutal Telling (Chief Inspector Gamache Series #5)|last=Noble|first=Barnes &|website=Barnes & Noble|language=en|access-date=2017-03-26}}</ref> owned by [[Macmillan Publishers]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://us.macmillan.com/thebrutaltelling/louisepenny/9781250109118/|title=The Brutal Telling {{!}} Louise Penny {{!}} Macmillan|work=US Macmillan|access-date=2017-03-26|language=en-US}}</ref>. The book was published on 22 September 2009, and later went on to win the [[Anthony Award]] for Best Novel in 2010.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bouchercon.com/anthony-awards/winners-and-nominees/|title=Winners and Nominees|date=2015-08-10|work=Bouchercon|access-date=2017-03-26|language=en}}</ref>
==Plot summary== The body of a man is found in the bistro in Three Pines. Investigations lead to a mysterious cottage in the nearby woods. Greed and revenge play a part.
