'''Voice casting''' is a vital pre-production process for selecting the [[voice talent]] for [[radio]] and [[television]] [[commercials]], [[Documentary film|documentary]] and [[corporate]] [[narrations]], [[audiobook]]s and [[online tutorials]]. It involves a series of [[auditions]] in front of a [[Film producer|producer]]/[[Film director|director]].
==Online voice casting== There has been a shift to online voice over casting in recent years. With many professional voice talent utilizing home studios,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peterdrewvo.com/html/home_voiceover_studio.html|title=Home Voiceover Studios-Equipping Yours-Peter Drew Voiceovers|publisher=}}</ref> clients are able to cut out traditional bricks and mortar agents. Websites devoted exclusively to pre-screened professional voice over talent are servicing international clients often faster and cheaper than the traditional casting process of voice talent physically being required to be in a studio.
